Interaction-style independent design principles Interaction-style independent design principles Strive for consistency (constancy is a special type ) a) internal; b) external with metaphor, and other software leads to higher conformity with user expectations Provide advance information Provide immediate feedback Permit easy reversal of actions (undo) Prevent errors; offer help in case of errors Reduce short-term memory load Cater to user diversity; allow for personalization (Let the user be in control)